ersuchungen zu heldenepischer Fassungsbildung und Varianz zur Verfügung gestellt  aVirginal narrates a youthful tale by Dietrich von Bern: the liberation of Queen Virginal from a cruel heathen captor and other battles with heathens, giants, and dragons. The new edition offers three versions of the adventurous epic that differ in scope, wording, and the constitution of meaning, along with the thematically related Goldemar fragment.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEpic poetry, GermanxHistory and criticism. 0aEpic poetry, German. 0aGerman poetryyMiddle High German, 1050-1500. 0aHeldensage. 4aDietrich von Bern. 4aEdition. 4aHeldenepik. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Medieval.2bisacsh  aEdition.  aMiddle High German heroic epics.  aepics of the Dietrich von Bern cycle.1 aLienert, Elisabeth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPontini, Elisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchumacher, Katrin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2017 Part 1z978311076249508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2017z9783110548198oZDB-23-DKU0 cprintz978311047678140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110477931zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110477931zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/